With the Dell U2713HM, users should be able to set their monitor provided Color 
Preset profiles also using ddccontrol.  The available Color Preset profiles 
with this model are; Standard, Multimedia, Movie, Game, Text, Color Temp. (w/ 
specifying an additional 5k-10k value), sRGB, Custom Color (w/ specifying R 
0-100, G 0-100, B 0-100 values).

Users can then script something to activate a specified display/monitor Color 
Profile automatically when using such applications.  For example, when using 
mplayer the monitor can be set to use the Movie color profile, or when using 
vim/gvim set the monitor to use the Text color profile.

Obviously though, we (or just I) currently don't know the hex address of the 
Color Preset profiles, nor the other addresses related to the secondary options 
of some of those Color Preset profiles.

Dell currently has a simple MS Windows taskbar application (ie.  
ddmsetup1445.exe) doing this for users, along with some other simple perks.


