I think I've gotten my Dell U2713HM to switch profiles using the following 
commands:

Switch to sRGB color profile:
# ddccontrol -p -r 0x14 -w 1

Uknown
# ddccontrol -p -r 0x14 -w 2
# ddccontrol -p -r 0x14 -w 3

Switch to (my preset #1) Color Temp 5000K profile:
# ddccontrol -p -r 0x14 -w 4

Switch to Color Temp 6500K profile:
# ddccontrol -p -r 0x14 -w 4

Switch to Color Temp 7500K (Simlar to Game Preset)
# ddccontrol -p -r 0x14 -w 5

Unknown
# ddccontrol -p -r 0x14 -w 6
# ddccontrol -p -r 0x14 -w 7

Switch to Color Temp 9300K
# ddccontrol -p -r 0x14 -w 8

Switch to Color Temp 10000K
# ddccontrol -p -r 0x14 -w 9

Unknown
# ddccontrol -p -r 0x14 -w 10

Switch to Color Temp 5700K
# ddccontrol -p -r 0x14 -w 11

Switch to Custom Color (100% R, 100% G, 100% B)
# ddccontrol -p -r 0x14 -w 12


It would appear some of the (Multimedia, Movie, Text, ...) color profile 
addresses are already written within another ddccontrol database 
display/monitor profile:

/usr/share/ddccontrol-db/monitor/DEL4063.xml

Now just to figure out what is being activated within the display/monitor, as 
there doesn't appear to be any realtime status displayed within the monitor, 
aside from comparing ddccontrol probes after manually changing the color preset 
modes.

After playing with the above values, can diff log files to find which values 
the monitor/display is changing when switching Color Preset Modes.  For 
example:

First, I switch to my custom color 5000K temperature preset on the 
display/monitor and then execute the following to probe the current values from 
the monitor:
# LANG= LC_ALL= ddccontrol -p -c -d > /tmp/ddccontrol-MyPresetTemp.log 2>&1

Then I switch my monitor Color Preset Mode to "Movie", and then execute the 
follow:
# LANG= LC_ALL= ddccontrol -p -c -d > /tmp/ddccontrol-Movia.log 2>&1

Next, diff the two files to find which values have changed:
# diff -uN /tmp/ddccontrol-MyPresetTemp.log /tmp/ddccontrol-Movia.log

After also doing the same with the Game color preset mode, it's interesting to 
note, aside from the 0x14 address from changing to 5, two other 0xdc & 0xe2 
addresses have changed.  (One would assume with the Dell U2713HM presets, there 
would be an address containing two numbers associated for the presets.  
Instead, the presets are set via a more intricate mechanism? Or maybe the 
register is found or displayed using ddccontrol yet?)


A little more research into the "/usr/share/ddccontrol-db/monitor/DEL4063.xml", 
and the 0xdc is for also specifying some of the modes;  "Multimedia = 2, Movie 
= 3", "Game = 5".  The following respectively sets these:

# ddccontrol -p -r 0xdc -w 2
# ddccontrol -p -r 0xdc -w 3
# ddccontrol -p -r 0xdc -w 5

I'm a little confused why the need for seperate 0x14 (sRGB/color_temp modes) 
and 0xdc (game/movie/multimedia modes) registers, and wondering why there's 255 
values for 0xdc (game/multimedia color modes), shrugs.  Guessing the 0x14 
specifies warmer colors, and the 0xdc register deals with blue/colder colors 
which are usually desired for Movies and Photos.  Guessing specialized filters.

I did notice, Standard color mode requires multiple register addresses to be 
changed; and no one register seemed to trigger the "Standard" color mode.  
Roughly five registers had to be changed.

Also note, almost all the above registers for (Multimedia, Movie, Game, Text, 
Color Temp, sRGB, and Custom Color) preset Color Modes, had other additional 
registers values changed, similar to specifying the previously mentioned 
Standard preset color mode.  (ie.  Such registers as Brightness and Contrast 
were changed, while Standard preset color more had several additional registers 
changed.)

Anyways, hopefully I've wet the appitite of some to perform more 
experimentation! :-)

